        "question": "Was City of Evil Grammy-nominated?",
        "answer": "Yes. \"Beast and the Harlot\" from Avenged Sevenfold's City of Evil (2005) received a Grammy nomination for Best Hard Rock Performance at the 48th Grammy Awards in 2006. It was A7X's first Grammy nomination and confirmed the album's mainstream cultural reach. City of Evil debuted at #30 on the Billboard 200 and achieved Platinum certification in the United States. It peaked at #22 in the UK and drove the band's first significant international audience."
