        "question": "What cymbals did The Rev play on City of Evil?",
        "answer": "The Rev played Zildjian A Custom cymbals on City of Evil (2005). His setup included Zildjian A Custom 14\" hi-hats, 16\", 18\", and 19\" crashes, a 20\" Ping ride (or A Custom equivalent), and an 18\" A Custom China. The Zildjian A Custom series — B20 bronze alloy with computer-guided lathing — produces a bright, cutting tone that projects above heavy guitar frequencies. The A Custom was The Rev's signature cymbal choice throughout his A7X career, including on the self-titled Avenged Sevenfold album (2007)."
