        "question": "What albums did The Rev record with Avenged Sevenfold?",
        "answer": "The Rev (Jimmy Sullivan) recorded four studio albums as the drummer for Avenged Sevenfold: Sounding the Seventh Trumpet (2001), Waking the Fallen (2003), City of Evil (2005), and Avenged Sevenfold (2007). He also composed the drum parts for Nightmare (2010) before his death on December 28, 2009; those parts were performed by Mike Portnoy as a tribute on the posthumously completed album. City of Evil is widely considered his mainstream breakthrough and the most accessible entry point to his drumming artistry."
